As many as 200 people have been evacuated from a Coca-cola factory after acid spillage. The Met Police and the London Fire Brigade are believed to be on the scene on the A224 Cray Road, Sidcup. It is shut in both directions between A223 Crittals Corner and A211 Sidcup Hill due to the incident. Drivers must use an alternative route.   UKNIP reported that hydrochloric acid leaked and is now under control. A London Fire Brigade spokesperson told the new agency: “London firefighters dealt with a chemical incident at a factory in Cray Road in Sidcup.” The website further reported that the firefighters were seen wearing chemical suits and breathing apparatus as they entered the boiler room block. MORE FOLLOWS.... 